-- Concretus Materials Seeks 51% of Cemex Lithuanian Associate: BNS
-- B y   B r y a n   B r a d l e y
-- 2013-01-02T10:40:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-02/concretus-materials-seeks-51-of-cemex-lithuanian-associate-bns.html
UAB Concretus Materials is seeking
regulatory approval to buy a majority of the Lithuanian cement
maker Akmenes Cementas AB that is one-third owned by  Cemex SAB (CX) 
of Mexico,  Baltic News Service  reported.  Concretus Materials, a Lithuanian company established in
September, submitted a request for permission to acquire as much
as 51 percent of Akmenes Cementas on Dec. 27, the newswire said
today, citing the Competition Council in Vilnius.  Akmenes Cementas plans by mid-2013 to complete expansion
and modernization projects worth 350 million litai ($134
million), according to BNS. In 2011, it produced 984,000 tons of
cement, of which 55 percent was sold in  Lithuania , BNS said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bryan Bradley in Vilnius at 
 bbradley13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
